    ],
    "summary": "On 17 February 2023 at approximately 0315 hours, a gas leak occurred on a 12-inch gas pipeline riser (PSN 759) approximately 5-7 feet above the water line at the WD 73AT production platform. The ESD was activated, shutting down the entire facility. All 26 personnel on board mustered upwind at the quarters structure and sheltered in place due to severe weather conditions (5-8 foot seas, 20-30 knot winds with gusts to 40 knots). The pipeline was bled down from 1080 psi to 0 psi. A light non-recoverable sheen (2.56 miles long, 300 feet wide) was observed during overflight. Investigation determined the leak was caused by inadequate preventative maintenance, with repairs identified in a 2015 Level 2 survey never completed, and inadequate inspection methods (drone survey on 15 Feb 2023 insufficient, no intelligent PIG inspection conducted).",
    "recommendations": [],
